<br>
Before SI came out, mercenaries levelled from 40-45 at Pygmy Goblins in Lyonesse. Every single one of them wore the chain of Banded Coral, but as four different classes use chainmail, and one is a tank, one a healer and one a rogue, they were pretty screwed. In fact the same can be said of most Albion chain drops.<br>
<br>
There seems to be no more variety among chainmail drops than there is in plate- the problem is that only two classes wear plate, and they're both tanks. Most Armsmen didn't mind a couple of peity points wasted, so long as they got their Parry, Str and Con.<br>
<br>
I actually don't have SI myself (don't see the need for it, I'm no crafter and my PC is pretty crappy as it is) , so I can't debate the usefulness of the SI drops. But it seems that there's not much mroe useful bracers and rings in SI, otherwise people would be talking about them all the time. The Tinctor Family Seal (+3 parry) sounds good, but I don't know how easy it is to get. I hope not too difficult, otherwise the options look like:<br>
<br>
The ring from the Green Knight- get 3fg and let's move...<br>
A lvl 35 ring from Lyonesse which gives 2parry and a load of Friar skills. There is a similar cloak.<br>
Our epic cloak sucks. Nobody uses it. There seem to be no cloaks designed for the mercenary.<br>
The same goes for bracers. When I was levelling up most mercs around me used lvl 29 Catacombs bracers for 1 parry and 1DW each.<br>
<br>
A lack of weapons which add (weapon) as well as DW, compare to all the polearms with +pole and shields with +themself, etc.<br>
Small and Medium Shields seem to receive inferior stats to Large Shields, and be lower level items. Check out the Dartmoor ones for an example of this hierarchy.<br>
<br>
All in all, it would just be nice if a few more items were designed with our class in mind. Both armour and accessories.<br>
<br>
